GRAMMARLY.name: Grammarly (Superhuman)
GRAMMARLY.tagline: Helping people communicate more effectively with AI-powered writing assistance across every platform
GRAMMARLY.overview: Grammarly is an AI-powered writing assistant founded in 2009 by Ukrainian entrepreneurs Max Lytvyn, Alex Shevchenko, and Dmytro Lider. The company reached $13B valuation in 2021 and $700M+ ARR in 2025. In May 2025, Grammarly raised $1B in non-dilutive financing from General Catalyst. In December 2024, Grammarly acquired Coda and brought on Shishir Mehrotra (ex-YouTube VP) as CEO. The company is rebranding to Superhuman in late 2025 as it pivots from writing assistant to full AI productivity platform. Over 30 million daily active users across 500,000+ teams globally.

products.name: Grammarly Editor
products.description: AI writing assistant for web and desktop

highlights.text: Raised $1B non-dilutive financing from General Catalyst (May 2025)
Acquired Coda, installed Shishir Mehrotra as CEO (Dec 2024)

GUSTO.name: Gusto
GUSTO.tagline: Simplifying payroll, benefits, and HR so small businesses can focus on their people and growth
GUSTO.overview: Gusto is a payroll, benefits, and HR platform for small businesses, founded in 2011 by Josh Reeves, Tomer London, and Edward Kim. The company serves 400,000+ SMBs and processes payroll for 6M+ workers. In 2024, revenue reached $735M (up 33% YoY) and the company has been free cash flow positive since early 2023. Gusto completed a $200M+ tender offer at $9.3B valuation in July 2025. Key 2025 highlights include the $600M acquisition of Guideline (retirement plans) and a global hiring partnership with Remote.

GROQ.name: Groq
GROQ.tagline: AI hardware company building Language Processing Units (LPUs) for ultra-fast AI inference
GROQ.overview: Groq is an AI hardware company founded in 2016 by former Google engineers, led by Jonathan Ross, one of the designers of Google's TPU. The company develops Language Processing Units (LPUs), specialized chips designed for AI inference that deliver exceptional speed, quality, and energy efficiency. As of September 2025, Groq has achieved a valuation of $6.9 billion following its latest funding round. The company offers both cloud-based (GroqCloud) and on-premises solutions, serving nearly 2 million developers and teams globally with sub-millisecond latency for AI inference.
